0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4247em;margin-left:-0.0359em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2753em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0894em;vertical-align:-0.2753em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4247em;margin-left:-0.0359em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2753em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>","key":"fuW9u0pWcX"},{"type":"text","value":", we will assume that X and Y are independent, or it will be clear from the context of the problem.","position":{"start":{"line":38,"column":1},"end":{"line":38,"column":1}},"key":"RSHxNknwnI"}],"key":"rTu4A7hpsq"},{"type":"admonition","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Example: Combined Mean and Standard Deviation","position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":1},"end":{"line":40,"column":1}},"key":"F3oEjmuIh5"}],"key":"TKYUfV8gjq"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"We want to find the mean and standard deviation of X + Y, the total number of defective products coming out of both production lines in an hour. In the previous section, we found that:\n\n$\\mu_{X}=1.8$\n\n$\\sigma_{X}=1.21$\n\n$\\mu_{Y}=2.7$\n\n$\\sigma_{Y}=0.85$\n\nUsing the rules for X + Y, we find that:\n\n$\\mu_{X+Y}=\\mu_{X}+\\mu_{Y}=1.8+2.7=4.5$\n\n$\\sigma_{X+Y}^{2}=\\sigma_{X}^{2}+\\sigma_{Y}^{2}=1.21^{2}+0.85^{2}=2.19$\n\n$\\sigma_{X+Y}=\\sqrt{2.19}=1.48$\n\nWe can conclude, then, that the total number of defective parts coming out of both production lines in an hour is on average 4.5, and typically the combined number of defective products is about 1.48 away from that average.","position":{"start":{"line":41,"column":1},"end":{"line":59,"column":1}},"key":"mPZVmRg9di"}],"key":"I7uhkHwVur"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":62,"column":1},"end":{"line":62,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Comment","position":{"start":{"line":62,"column":1},"end":{"line":62,"column":1}},"key":"qpnTHmbSop"}],"identifier":"comment","label":"Comment","html_id":"comment-1","implicit":true,"key":"ZkjmDGdNYr"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":64,"column":1},"end":{"line":64,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It is important to remember that while variances are additive, standard deviations are not:","position":{"start":{"line":64,"column":1},"end":{"line":64,"column":1}},"key":"QGnT2t6Khs"}],"key":"e7sfr6frOQ"},{"type":"paragraph","p